<subSubSection pageNumber="414" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="414">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="414">Note: 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coronarium">Chrysanthemum coronarium L.</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
had long been treated as the 
<typeStatus>generitype</typeStatus>
until Trehane (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="414">Taxon</emphasis>
44: 439. 1995) proposed the conservation of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="414">Chrysanthemum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="indicum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="414">C. indicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the conserved type, in order to restrict the generic name to the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="floristsâ€™">florists'</normalizedToken>
chrysanthemum. The proposal was successful, resulting in 
<taxonomicName authority="Cass" authorityName="Cass" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Glebionis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="414">Glebionis</emphasis>
Cass
</taxonomicName>
, becoming the correct generic name for 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="segetum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="414">C. segetum</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coronarium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="414">C. coronarium</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
